text: Galway West is a parliamentary constituency represented in Dáil Éireann, the lower house of the Irish parliament or Oireachtas. The constituency elects 5 deputies (Teachtaí Dála, commonly known as TDs). It was created in 1937. ==References== Category:20th-century establishments in the Republic of Ireland Category:1937 establishments in Europe Category:Politics of Ireland
